==== SOURCE

https://cloud.google.com/blog/products/g-suite/ridding-gmail-of-100-million-more-spam-messages-with-tensorflow

==== AGENT

Google

==== GOAL

Block spam emails

==== DATA

Spam emails being sent to users

==== METHODS

Supervised learning, emails tagged as spammed are used to teach the machine.

==== RESULTS

According to other sources, it worked out well.

==== COMMENTS

Google are using TensorFlow to further develop there already effective spam filter. Google's existing spam filter which utilises verious methods, including machine learning, already blocks more than 99.9% of spam mails. This effort is in order to block those few spam emails that make it through.